gomodel:SYNGO_456  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 5: The frequency of mEPSC was significantly increased in SCR-KO cultured neurons. mEPSC amplitude was not affected suggesting presynaptic role.\nFig 6F,G: The frequency of mEPSC was significantly increased in SCR-KO CA1 neurons in hippocampal slice preparations . mEPSC amplitude was not affected suggesting presynaptic role.\nFig 6B,C: Fbxl20/SCRAPPER Tunes Synaptic Transmission via Regulation of RIM: RIM KD in SCR-KO restores mEPSC frequency to WT levels.. Experimental description: M&M: Primary cultured neurons from SCR-KO **mice** were prepared with P1- P3 mice." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_456" ;
